io.foxtrot.common.core.models.route

Class Waypoint

  • Object
    • io.foxtrot.common.core.models.route.Waypoint

  • public class Waypoint
extends Object
    A Waypoint is an object that contains both the customer information, their Location, and a list of Delivery at the location.

    Fields:

    Name Type Required? Description
    customerId String true A globally unique identifier identifying the customer at this waypoint
    location Location true The geocode coordinate at this waypoint
    name String false The name of this waypoint
    address String false The address at this waypoint
    serviceTimeInSeconds Long false The estimated amount of time in seconds the driver will take to complete this waypoint
    deliveries List<Delivery> true The list of Delivery objects at this waypoint. This list must not be empty.
    timeWindows List<TimeWindow> true The list of TimeWindow objects at this waypoint. This list can be empty. 

    
   List<Delivery> deliveries = ...;
   List<TimeWindow> timeWindows = ...;
   Waypoint waypoint = Waypoint.builder()
                               .setLocation(Location.create(1.0, 2.0))
                               .setAddress("123 Fake St")
                               .setName("Whole Foods")
                               .setCustomerId("Customer Unique Id")
                               .setDeliveries(deliveries)
                               .setTimeWindows(timeWindows)
                               .setServiceTimeInSeconds(600L) // 10 minutes
                               .build();
    See Also:
    Waypoint.Builder
